components.content: Large herds will split up into small herds if there is not enough food and water.
Small herds then move away from each other to find food and water.
When there is a lot of food and water in an environment, elephants can live in large herds.
This is an example of how environments can change how animals live in groups.
All animals need food, water and shelter to survive.
